  "text": "Excuse me sir, sir, are you a millionaire? Not anymore. Did you go broke? No, I became a billionaire. You're a billionaire? How did you become a billionaire? Yeah, but who are you? I'm a billionaire all over the world. I've been even 44 billionaires as of right now. Can I interview you for a minute? Yeah, sure. Did you come from a lot of money? Were your parents rich? Definitely not. Definitely not rich. I always knew I was going to be successful. Do you have to be a little crazy to become this successful? Do I have to be crazy? Are you crazy? Tell me, tell me, are you crazy? No, I'm very level. But I did work 22 hours a day because I started that business and it was worth zero. And I sold it 20 years later for 1.5 billion. What business made you a billionaire? It was mobile phones. Mobile phones like Apple. No, not like Apple, no. I was a retailer and wholesaler all over the world. Are you a good salesman? No, I don't think you're going to get to where I am without being a good salesman. So what was your secret to sales? It's not a very comfortable word to use but you've got to be very manipulative because you've got to make the buyer realize you won't be beaten up. Were you ever afraid of competition? No, I was afraid of my suppliers because when you became too big the suppliers wanted to cut you off and they wanted to axe you and grow competitors to you because they had a favorite expression which is they don't want the tail wagging the dog and I became the dog. You know they don't teach this in school, right? They don't teach anything in school about entrepreneurship. Correct me if I'm wrong. Taxes are crazy in the UK. Do you have a tax hack for anybody in business? I believe that you should pay your taxes in the country that you've made your money in. So you paid your taxes. I paid all my taxes on the sale of the business. What's the most amount of money you paid in taxes in one year? 200 million. You paid 200 million in taxes? Yeah, and I could have avoided it. How? By moving to Monaco. Why did you not do that? Because I feel that the poor people need help. Why? A childhood dream I had when I was eight years old was that I would be driving around in a chauffeur-driven Rolls-Royce handing five pound notes out to poor people and that dream had to be fulfilled. Like I told my kids, I'm not bothered about you being rich. I want you to leave the world a better place than you found it and be happy. Thank you so much for your time, man. Thank you. I connect with all the billionaires at IndieView. Could I get your contact? Sure.",
